# --- Obsidian test vault ---
# Commit only the QA skeleton: the hot-reload tooling and the config that
# pre-enables the plugin. Everything else under .obsidian/ is generated by
# Obsidian on open (app.json, workspace.json, appearance.json, caches, …) and
# is per-developer churn — so default to ignoring all of it via an allowlist.

# Ignore everything Obsidian writes directly under .obsidian/ ...
/.obsidian/*
# ... but keep the intentional, committed config + tooling:
!/.obsidian/community-plugins.json
!/.obsidian/plugins/

# Inside plugins/, ignore everything except the committed hot-reload tooling.
# The plugin-under-test (newtab/) is deployed by `DEPLOY_VAULT=1 npm run build`
# and is excluded here — never commit the built artifact.
/.obsidian/plugins/*
!/.obsidian/plugins/hot-reload/

.trash/
